{"type":"message","id":"40ae8145","parentId":"9046bdbc","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:15.406Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m2z12hex0448_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"10:Agent-scoped configuration keys under `agents.*`, `multiAgent.*`, `session.*`,\n388:- `reasoningDefault`: default reasoning visibility for agents. Values: `\"off\"`, `\"on\"`, `\"stream\"`. Per-agent `agents.list[].reasoningDefault` overrides this default. Configured reasoning defaults are only applied for owners, authorized senders, or operator-admin gateway contexts when no per-message or session reasoning override is set.\n960:        reasoningDefault: \"on\", // per-agent reasoning visibility override\n1007:- `reasoningDefault`: optional per-agent default reasoning visibility (`on | off | stream`). Overrides `agents.defaults.reasoningDefault` for this agent when no per-message or session reasoning override is set."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"10:Agent-scoped configuration keys under `agents.*`, `multiAgent.*`, `session.*`,\n388:- `reasoningDefault`: default reasoning visibility for agents. Values: `\"off\"`, `\"on\"`, `\"stream\"`. Per-agent `agents.list[].reasoningDefault` overrides this default. Configured reasoning defaults are only applied for owners, authorized senders, or operator-admin gateway contexts when no per-message or session reasoning override is set.\n960:        reasoningDefault: \"on\", // per-agent reasoning visibility override\n1007:- `reasoningDefault`: optional per-agent default reasoning visibility (`on | off | stream`). Overrides `agents.defaults.reasoningDefault` for this agent when no per-message or session reasoning override is set.","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778903775406}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e338156","parentId":"40ae8145","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:15.406Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m2z12hex0448_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"10:Agent-scoped configuration keys under `agents.*`, `multiAgent.*`, `session.*`,\n14:## Agent defaults\n16:### `agents.defaults.workspace`\n26:### `agents.defaults.repoRoot`\n36:### `agents.defaults.skills`\n60:### `agents.defaults.skipBootstrap`\n70:### `agents.defaults.skipOptionalBootstrapFiles`\n84:### `agents.defaults.contextInjection`\n97:### `agents.defaults.bootstrapMaxChars`\n107:### `agents.defaults.bootstrapTotalMaxChars`\n117:### `agents.defaults.bootstrapPromptTruncationWarning`\n136:### Context budget ownership map\n162:#### `agents.defaults.startupContext`\n185:#### `agents.defaults.contextLimits`\n213:#### `agents.list[].contextLimits`\n240:#### `skills.limits.maxSkillsPromptChars`\n255:#### `agents.list[].skillsLimits.maxSkillsPromptChars`\n274:### `agents.defaults.imageMaxDimensionPx`\n288:### `agents.defaults.userTimezone`\n298:### `agents.defaults.timeFormat`\n308:### `agents.defaults.model`\n405:### `agents.defaults.agentRuntime`\n454:### `agents.defaults.cliBackends`\n489:### `agents.defaults.systemPromptOverride`\n503:### `agents.defaults.promptOverlays`\n525:### `agents.defaults.heartbeat`\n566:### `agents.defaults.compaction`\n614:### `agents.defaults.contextPruning`\n658:### Block streaming\n680:### Typing indicators\n700:### `agents.defaults.sandbox`\n938:### `agents.list` (per-agent overrides)\n1019:## Multi-agent routing\n1038:### Binding match fields\n1060:### Per-agent access profiles\n1159:## Session\n1239:## Messages\n1269:### Response prefix\n1287:### Ack reaction\n1298:### Inbound debounce"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":46,"aggregated":"10:Agent-scoped configuration keys under `agents.*`, `multiAgent.*`, `session.*`,\n14:## Agent defaults\n16:### `agents.defaults.workspace`\n26:### `agents.defaults.repoRoot`\n36:### `agents.defaults.skills`\n60:### `agents.defaults.skipBootstrap`\n70:### `agents.defaults.skipOptionalBootstrapFiles`\n84:### `agents.defaults.contextInjection`\n97:### `agents.defaults.bootstrapMaxChars`\n107:### `agents.defaults.bootstrapTotalMaxChars`\n117:### `agents.defaults.bootstrapPromptTruncationWarning`\n136:### Context budget ownership map\n162:#### `agents.defaults.startupContext`\n185:#### `agents.defaults.contextLimits`\n213:#### `agents.list[].contextLimits`\n240:#### `skills.limits.maxSkillsPromptChars`\n255:#### `agents.list[].skillsLimits.maxSkillsPromptChars`\n274:### `agents.defaults.imageMaxDimensionPx`\n288:### `agents.defaults.userTimezone`\n298:### `agents.defaults.timeFormat`\n308:### `agents.defaults.model`\n405:### `agents.defaults.agentRuntime`\n454:### `agents.defaults.cliBackends`\n489:### `agents.defaults.systemPromptOverride`\n503:### `agents.defaults.promptOverlays`\n525:### `agents.defaults.heartbeat`\n566:### `agents.defaults.compaction`\n614:### `agents.defaults.contextPruning`\n658:### Block streaming\n680:### Typing indicators\n700:### `agents.defaults.sandbox`\n938:### `agents.list` (per-agent overrides)\n1019:## Multi-agent routing\n1038:### Binding match fields\n1060:### Per-agent access profiles\n1159:## Session\n1239:## Messages\n1269:### Response prefix\n1287:### Ack reaction\n1298:### Inbound debounce","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778903775406}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb7fa339","parentId":"8e338156","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:20.033Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the multi-agent routing section and the tools section to understand how multi-agent visibility actually works in OpenClaw.\n","thinkingSignature":"c66db098e734d3cb39566ade8d0b856e76c6e43bb864cf86f0b493d67343c2da"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qfkzx4yx04mk_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":120,"offset":1019,"path":"/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":727,"output":91,"cacheRead":33344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34162,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778903775473,"responseId":"06571ddf493d623a091ce08b697e1fe4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"cbe6f7c7","parentId":"eb7fa339","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:20.056Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qfkzx4yx04mk_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Multi-agent routing\n\nRun multiple isolated agents inside one Gateway. See [Multi-Agent](/concepts/multi-agent).\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    list: [\n      { id: \"home\", default: true, workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-home\" },\n      { id: \"work\", workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-work\" },\n    ],\n  },\n  bindings: [\n    { agentId: \"home\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"personal\" } },\n    { agentId: \"work\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"biz\" } },\n  ],\n}\n```\n\n### Binding match fields\n\n- `type` (optional): `route` for normal routing (missing type defaults to route), `acp` for persistent ACP conversation bindings.\n- `match.channel` (required)\n- `match.accountId` (optional; `*` = any account; omitted = default account)\n- `match.peer` (optional; `{ kind: direct|group|channel, id }`)\n- `match.guildId` / `match.teamId` (optional; channel-specific)\n- `acp` (optional; only for `type: \"acp\"`): `{ mode, label, cwd, backend }`\n\n**Deterministic match order:**\n\n1. `match.peer`\n2. `match.guildId`\n3. `match.teamId`\n4. `match.accountId` (exact, no peer/guild/team)\n5. `match.accountId: \"*\"` (channel-wide)\n6. Default agent\n\nWithin each tier, the first matching `bindings` entry wins.\n\nFor `type: \"acp\"` entries, OpenClaw resolves by exact conversation identity (`match.channel` + account + `match.peer.id`) and does not use the route binding tier order above.\n\n### Per-agent access profiles\n\n<Accordion title=\"Full access (no sandbox)\">\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    list: [\n      {\n        id: \"personal\",\n        workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-personal\",\n        sandbox: { mode: \"off\" },\n      },\n    ],\n  },\n}\n```\n\n</Accordion>\n\n<Accordion title=\"Read-only tools + workspace\">\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    list: [\n      {\n        id: \"family\",\n        workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-family\",\n        sandbox: { mode: \"all\", scope: \"agent\", workspaceAccess: \"ro\" },\n        tools: {\n          allow: [\n            \"read\",\n            \"sessions_list\",\n            \"sessions_history\",\n            \"sessions_send\",\n            \"sessions_spawn\",\n            \"session_status\",\n          ],\n          deny: [\"write\", \"edit\", \"apply_patch\", \"exec\", \"process\", \"browser\"],\n        },\n      },\n    ],\n  },\n}\n```\n\n</Accordion>\n\n<Accordion title=\"No filesystem access (messaging only)\">\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    list: [\n      {\n        id: \"public\",\n        workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-public\",\n        sandbox: { mode: \"all\", scope: \"agent\", workspaceAccess: \"none\" },\n        tools: {\n          allow: [\n            \"sessions_list\",\n            \"sessions_history\",\n            \"sessions_send\",\n            \"sessions_spawn\",\n            \"session_status\",\n            \"whatsapp\",\n            \"telegram\",\n            \"slack\",\n            \"discord\",\n            \"gateway\",\n          ],\n          deny: [\n            \"read\",\n            \"write\",\n            \"edit\",\n            \"apply_patch\",\n            \"exec\",\n            \"process\",\n\n[271 more lines in file. Use offset=1139 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778903780055}}
{"type":"message","id":"03b6820e","parentId":"cbe6f7c7","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:24.410Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me look at the session visibility section to understand the current config structure:\n","thinkingSignature":"9925764f0eeaec0551160c4220c1b81082940d7718827ec1d9c50a1178b73605"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rdv51mmg1lpm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":100,"offset":1159,"path":"/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":875,"output":81,"cacheRead":34048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35004,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778903780092,"responseId":"06571de49de286b63d5f57f9cf0b1270"}}
{"type":"message","id":"82c615e7","parentId":"03b6820e","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:24.433Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rdv51mmg1lpm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Session\n\n```json5\n{\n  session: {\n    scope: \"per-sender\",\n    dmScope: \"main\", // main | per-peer | per-channel-peer | per-account-channel-peer\n    identityLinks: {\n      alice: [\"telegram:123456789\", \"discord:987654321012345678\"],\n    },\n    reset: {\n      mode: \"daily\", // daily | idle\n      atHour: 4,\n      idleMinutes: 60,\n    },\n    resetByType: {\n      thread: { mode: \"daily\", atHour: 4 },\n      direct: { mode: \"idle\", idleMinutes: 240 },\n      group: { mode: \"idle\", idleMinutes: 120 },\n    },\n    resetTriggers: [\"/new\", \"/reset\"],\n    store: \"~/.openclaw/agents/{agentId}/sessions/sessions.json\",\n    maintenance: {\n      mode: \"warn\", // warn | enforce\n      pruneAfter: \"30d\",\n      maxEntries: 500,\n      resetArchiveRetention: \"30d\", // duration or false\n      maxDiskBytes: \"500mb\", // optional hard budget\n      highWaterBytes: \"400mb\", // optional cleanup target\n    },\n    threadBindings: {\n      enabled: true,\n      idleHours: 24, // default inactivity auto-unfocus in hours (`0` disables)\n      maxAgeHours: 0, // default hard max age in hours (`0` disables)\n    },\n    mainKey: \"main\", // legacy (runtime always uses \"main\")\n    agentToAgent: { maxPingPongTurns: 5 },\n    sendPolicy: {\n      rules: [{ action: \"deny\", match: { channel: \"discord\", chatType: \"group\" } }],\n      default: \"allow\",\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n<Accordion title=\"Session field details\">\n\n- **`scope`**: base session grouping strategy for group-chat contexts.\n  - `per-sender` (default): each sender gets an isolated session within a channel context.\n  - `global`: all participants in a channel context share a single session (use only when shared context is intended).\n- **`dmScope`**: how DMs are grouped.\n  - `main`: all DMs share the main session.\n  - `per-peer`: isolate by sender id across channels.\n  - `per-channel-peer`: isolate per channel + sender (recommended for multi-user inboxes).\n  - `per-account-channel-peer`: isolate per account + channel + sender (recommended for multi-account).\n- **`identityLinks`**: map canonical ids to provider-prefixed peers for cross-channel session sharing. Dock commands such as `/dock_discord` use the same map to switch the active session's reply route to another linked channel peer; see [Channel docking](/concepts/channel-docking).\n- **`reset`**: primary reset policy. `daily` resets at `atHour` local time; `idle` resets after `idleMinutes`. When both configured, whichever expires first wins. Daily reset freshness uses the session row's `sessionStartedAt`; idle reset freshness uses `lastInteractionAt`. Background/system-event writes such as heartbeat, cron wakeups, exec notifications, and gateway bookkeeping can update `updatedAt`, but they do not keep daily/idle sessions fresh.\n- **`resetByType`**: per-type overrides (`direct`, `group`, `thread`). Legacy `dm` accepted as alias for `direct`.\n- **`mainKey`**: legacy field. Runtime always uses `\"main\"` for the main direct-chat bucket.\n- **`agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns`**: maximum reply-back turns between agents during agent-to-agent exchanges (integer, range: `0`–`5`). `0` disables ping-pong chaining.\n- **`sendPolicy`**: match by `channel`, `chatType` (`direct|group|channel`, with legacy `dm` alias), `keyPrefix`, or `rawKeyPrefix`. First deny wins.\n- **`maintenance`**: session-store cleanup + retention controls.\n  - `mode`: `warn` emits warnings only; `enforce` applies cleanup.\n  - `pruneAfter`: age cutoff for stale entries (default `30d`).\n  - `maxEntries`: maximum number of entries in `sessions.json` (default `500`). Runtime writes batch cleanup with a small high-water buffer for production-sized caps; `openclaw sessions cleanup --enforce` applies the cap immediately.\n  - `rotateBytes`: deprecated and ignored; `openclaw doctor --fix` removes it from older configs.\n  - `resetArchiveRetention`: retention for `*.reset.<timestamp>` transcript archives. Defaults to `pruneAfter`; set `false` to disable.\n  - `maxDiskBytes`: optional sessions-directory disk budget. In `warn` mode it logs warnings; in `enforce` mode it removes oldest artifacts/sessions first.\n  - `highWaterBytes`: optional target after budget cleanup. Defaults to `80%` of `maxDiskBytes`.\n- **`threadBindings`**: global defaults for thread-bound session features.\n  - `enabled`: master default switch (providers can override; Discord uses `channels.discord.threadBindings.enabled`)\n  - `idleHours`: default inactivity auto-unfocus in hours (`0` disables; providers can override)\n  - `maxAgeHours`: default hard max age in hours (`0` disables; providers can override)\n  - `spawnSessions`: default gate for creating thread-bound work sessions from `sessions_spawn` and ACP thread spawns. Defaults to `true` when thread bindings are enabled; providers/accounts can override.\n  - `defaultSpawnContext`: default native subagent context for thread-bound spawns (`\"fork\"` or `\"isolated\"`). Defaults to `\"fork\"`.\n\n</Accordion>\n\n---\n\n## Messages\n\n```json5\n{\n  messages: {\n    responsePrefix: \"🦞\", // or \"auto\"\n    ackReaction: \"👀\",\n    ackReactionScope: \"group-mentions\", // group-mentions | group-all | direct | all\n    removeAckAfterReply: false,\n    queue: {\n      mode: \"steer\", // steer | queue (legacy one-at-a-time) | followup | collect | steer-backlog | steer+backlog | interrupt\n      debounceMs: 500,\n      cap: 20,\n      drop: \"summarize\", // old | new | summarize\n      byChannel: {\n        whatsapp: \"steer\",\n        telegram: \"steer\",\n      },\n    },\n    inbound: {\n\n[151 more lines in file. Use offset=1259 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778903784433}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a0fac88","parentId":"82c615e7","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:33.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I've seen the actual config schema. There's no `multi_agent_enable`, `agent_chat_visible`, or `share_context_pool` anywhere in the actual docs. The user is citing configuration keys that simply don't exist in OpenClaw.\n\nLet me check the Session section more carefully - I saw `agentToAgent` and `sendPolicy` but those are not what the user described.\n\nLet me also check the tools config for `sessions.visibility` which I saw in the actual config.","thinkingSignature":"452bfaa6b0b3c25eeaea0dba2cfedb4741ea2bcf8ede30ba378a68dcdb1f1e4b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7ckb8v06hvji_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"tools\\|sessions\\|visibility\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"visibility\\|all\\|session\" | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1466,"output":172,"cacheRead":34912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36550,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778903784449,"responseId":"06571de81abfd0a589ab4a7e2a21c1cf"}}
{"type":"message","id":"acdc3d52","parentId":"4a0fac88","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:33.058Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7ckb8v06hvji_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"388:- `reasoningDefault`: default reasoning visibility for agents. Values: `\"off\"`, `\"on\"`, `\"stream\"`. Per-agent `agents.list[].reasoningDefault` overrides this default. Configured reasoning defaults are only applied for owners, authorized senders, or operator-admin gateway contexts when no per-message or session reasoning override is set.\n403:- `maxConcurrent`: max parallel agent runs across sessions (each session still serialized). Default: 4.\n432:- Harness choice is pinned per session id after the first embedded run. Config/env changes affect new or reset sessions, not an existing transcript. Legacy sessions with transcript history but no recorded pin are treated as PI-pinned. `/status` reports the effective runtime, for example `Runtime: OpenClaw Pi Default` or `Runtime: OpenAI Codex`.\n784:          \"sessions_list\",\n785:          \"sessions_history\",\n786:          \"sessions_send\",\n787:          \"sessions_spawn\",\n891:- `allowHostControl: false` (default) blocks sandboxed sessions from targeting the host browser.\n960:        reasoningDefault: \"on\", // per-agent reasoning visibility override\n1007:- `reasoningDefault`: optional per-agent default reasoning visibility (`on | off | stream`). Overrides `agents.defaults.reasoningDefault` for this agent when no per-message or session reasoning override is set.\n1010:- `runtime`: optional per-agent runtime descriptor. Use `type: \"acp\"` with `runtime.acp` defaults (`agent`, `backend`, `mode`, `cwd`) when the agent should default to ACP harness sessions.\n1013:- `subagents.allowAgents`: allowlist of agent ids for explicit `sessions_spawn.agentId` targets (`[\"*\"]` = any; default: same agent only). Include the requester id when self-targeted `agentId` calls should be allowed.\n1014:- Sandbox inheritance guard: if the requester session is sandboxed, `sessions_spawn` rejects targets that would run unsandboxed.\n1015:- `subagents.requireAgentId`: when true, block `sessions_spawn` calls that omit `agentId` (forces explicit profile selection; default: false).\n1093:            \"sessions_list\",\n1094:            \"sessions_history\",\n1095:            \"sessions_send\",\n1096:            \"sessions_spawn\",\n1121:            \"sessions_list\",\n1122:            \"sessions_history\",\n1123:            \"sessions_send\",\n1124:            \"sessions_spawn\",\n1180:    store: \"~/.openclaw/agents/{agentId}/sessions/sessions.json\",\n1215:- **`reset`**: primary reset policy. `daily` resets at `atHour` local time; `idle` resets after `idleMinutes`. When both configured, whichever expires first wins. Daily reset freshness uses the session row's `sessionStartedAt`; idle reset freshness uses `lastInteractionAt`. Background/system-event writes such as heartbeat, cron wakeups, exec notifications, and gateway bookkeeping can update `updatedAt`, but they do not keep daily/idle sessions fresh.\n1223:  - `maxEntries`: maximum number of entries in `sessions.json` (default `500`). Runtime writes batch cleanup with a small high-water buffer for production-sized caps; `openclaw sessions cleanup --enforce` applies the cap immediately.\n1226:  - `maxDiskBytes`: optional sessions-directory disk budget. In `warn` mode it logs warnings; in `enforce` mode it removes oldest artifacts/sessions first.\n1232:  - `spawnSessions`: default gate for creating thread-bound work sessions from `sessions_spawn` and ACP thread spawns. Defaults to `true` when thread bindings are enabled; providers/accounts can override."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":23,"aggregated":"388:- `reasoningDefault`: default reasoning visibility for agents. Values: `\"off\"`, `\"on\"`, `\"stream\"`. Per-agent `agents.list[].reasoningDefault` overrides this default. Configured reasoning defaults are only applied for owners, authorized senders, or operator-admin gateway contexts when no per-message or session reasoning override is set.\n403:- `maxConcurrent`: max parallel agent runs across sessions (each session still serialized). Default: 4.\n432:- Harness choice is pinned per session id after the first embedded run. Config/env changes affect new or reset sessions, not an existing transcript. Legacy sessions with transcript history but no recorded pin are treated as PI-pinned. `/status` reports the effective runtime, for example `Runtime: OpenClaw Pi Default` or `Runtime: OpenAI Codex`.\n784:          \"sessions_list\",\n785:          \"sessions_history\",\n786:          \"sessions_send\",\n787:          \"sessions_spawn\",\n891:- `allowHostControl: false` (default) blocks sandboxed sessions from targeting the host browser.\n960:        reasoningDefault: \"on\", // per-agent reasoning visibility override\n1007:- `reasoningDefault`: optional per-agent default reasoning visibility (`on | off | stream`). Overrides `agents.defaults.reasoningDefault` for this agent when no per-message or session reasoning override is set.\n1010:- `runtime`: optional per-agent runtime descriptor. Use `type: \"acp\"` with `runtime.acp` defaults (`agent`, `backend`, `mode`, `cwd`) when the agent should default to ACP harness sessions.\n1013:- `subagents.allowAgents`: allowlist of agent ids for explicit `sessions_spawn.agentId` targets (`[\"*\"]` = any; default: same agent only). Include the requester id when self-targeted `agentId` calls should be allowed.\n1014:- Sandbox inheritance guard: if the requester session is sandboxed, `sessions_spawn` rejects targets that would run unsandboxed.\n1015:- `subagents.requireAgentId`: when true, block `sessions_spawn` calls that omit `agentId` (forces explicit profile selection; default: false).\n1093:            \"sessions_list\",\n1094:            \"sessions_history\",\n1095:            \"sessions_send\",\n1096:            \"sessions_spawn\",\n1121:            \"sessions_list\",\n1122:            \"sessions_history\",\n1123:            \"sessions_send\",\n1124:            \"sessions_spawn\",\n1180:    store: \"~/.openclaw/agents/{agentId}/sessions/sessions.json\",\n1215:- **`reset`**: primary reset policy. `daily` resets at `atHour` local time; `idle` resets after `idleMinutes`. When both configured, whichever expires first wins. Daily reset freshness uses the session row's `sessionStartedAt`; idle reset freshness uses `lastInteractionAt`. Background/system-event writes such as heartbeat, cron wakeups, exec notifications, and gateway bookkeeping can update `updatedAt`, but they do not keep daily/idle sessions fresh.\n1223:  - `maxEntries`: maximum number of entries in `sessions.json` (default `500`). Runtime writes batch cleanup with a small high-water buffer for production-sized caps; `openclaw sessions cleanup --enforce` applies the cap immediately.\n1226:  - `maxDiskBytes`: optional sessions-directory disk budget. In `warn` mode it logs warnings; in `enforce` mode it removes oldest artifacts/sessions first.\n1232:  - `spawnSessions`: default gate for creating thread-bound work sessions from `sessions_spawn` and ACP thread spawns. Defaults to `true` when thread bindings are enabled; providers/accounts can override.","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778903793058}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d18c9d9","parentId":"acdc3d52","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:41.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me search for the tools config with sessions.visibility specifically in the config reference.","thinkingSignature":"370329dfd60bf021861aab1ec6940a04649bac185adf07971ace3a067d77b95a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ape48luhbq8o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A 20 \"^## Tools\\b\\|^### tools\\|\\\"tools\\\"\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md 2>/dev/null | head -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ape48luhbq8o_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -B 2 -A 10 \"sessions.*visibility\\|visibility.*session\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":885,"output":145,"cacheRead":36352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37382,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778903793076,"responseId":"06571df11e8e390dc512f85237c28b0c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce974b0d","parentId":"5d18c9d9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:56:41.287Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ape48luhbq8o_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Tools and custom providers\n\nTool policy, experimental toggles, provider-backed tool config, and custom\nprovider / base-URL setup moved to a dedicated page — see\n[Configuration — tools and custom providers](/gateway/config-tools).\n\n## Models\n\nProvider definitions, model allowlists, and custom provider setup live in\n[Configuration — tools and custom providers](/gateway/config-tools#custom-providers-and-base-urls).\nThe `models` root also owns global model-catalog behavior.\n\n```json5\n{\n  models: {\n    // Optional. Default: true. Requires a Gateway restart when changed.\n    pricing: { enabled: false },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n--\n    redactSensitive: \"tools\", // off | tools\n    redactPatterns: [\"\\\\bTOKEN\\\\b\\\\s*[=:]\\\\s*([\\\"']?)([^\\\\s\\\"']+)\\\\1\"],\n  },\n}\n```\n\n- Default log file: `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-YYYY-MM-DD.log`.\n- Set `logging.file` for a stable path.\n- `consoleLevel` bumps to `debug` when `--verbose`.\n- `maxFileBytes`: maximum active log file size in bytes before rotation (positive integer; default: `104857600` = 100 MB). OpenClaw keeps up to five numbered archives beside the active file.\n- `redactSensitive` / `redactPatterns`: best-effort masking for console output, file logs, OTLP log records, and persisted session transcript text. `redactSensitive: \"off\"` only disables this general log/transcript policy; UI/tool/diagnostic safety surfaces still redact secrets before emission.\n\n---\n\n## Diagnostics\n\n```json5\n{\n  diagnostics: {\n    enabled: true,\n    flags: [\"telegram.*\"],"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":37,"aggregated":"## Tools and custom providers\n\nTool policy, experimental toggles, provider-backed tool config, and custom\nprovider / base-URL setup moved to a dedicated page — see\n[Configuration — tools and custom providers](/gateway/config-tools).\n\n## Models\n\nProvider definitions, model allowlists, and custom provider setup live in\n[Configuration — tools and custom providers](/gateway/config-tools#custom-providers-and-base-urls).\nThe `models` root also owns global model-catalog behavior.\n\n```json5\n{\n  models: {\n    // Optional. Default: true. Requires a Gateway restart when changed.\n    pricing: { enabled: false },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n--\n    redactSensitive: \"tools\", // off | tools\n    redactPatterns: [\"\\\\bTOKEN\\\\b\\\\s*[=:]\\\\s*([\\\"']?)([^\\\\s\\\"']+)\\\\1\"],\n  },\n}\n```\n\n- Default log file: `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-YYYY-MM-DD.log`.\n- Set `logging.file` for a stable path.\n- `consoleLevel` bumps to `debug` when `--verbose`.\n- `maxFileBytes`: maximum active log file size in bytes before rotation (positive integer; default: `104857600` = 100 MB). OpenClaw keeps up to five numbered archives beside the active file.\n- `redactSensitive` / `redactPatterns`: best-effort masking for console output, file logs, OTLP log records, and persisted session transcript text. `redactSensitive: \"off\"` only disables this general log/transcript policy; UI/tool/diagnostic safety surfaces still redact secrets before emission.\n\n---\n\n## Diagnostics\n\n```json5\n{\n  diagnostics: {\n    enabled: true,\n    flags: [\"telegram.*\"],","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778903801287}}
