{"type":"message","id":"f3d7b83a","parentId":"ecbf5bd4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T08:53:11.094Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `workspace-tts` exists as a directory but doesn't have the memory files or MEMORY.md. Let me check if the tts agent has a workspace configured properly. Looking at the config, the tts agent has `\"workspace\": \"workspace-tts\"` - that's a relative path. But there's no memory directory in workspace-tts.\n\nThe main workspace has:\n- MEMORY.md\n- memory/ directory\n- DREAMS.md\n- etc.\n\nBut the workspace-tts directory doesn't seem to have these files. This is the problem - the tts agent doesn't have its own MEMORY.md or daily memory files.\n\nIn OpenClaw, each agent's memory works like:\n1. Session transcript (what was said in the conversation)\n2. Session compaction (summarization of past conversations)\n3. Workspace memory files (MEMORY.md, memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md)\n\nThe tts agent might not be properly preserving memory because:\n\n\n1. It lacks a MEMORY.md file in its workspace\n2. It might not be generating daily memory files\n3. Session compaction might be the issue - if compaction is set to \"safeguard\" mode in the config, it could be clearing session history too aggressively\n\nI need to check what compaction settings are actually configured for the tts agent and whether it has the necessary workspace files to maintain persistent memory.","thinkingSignature":"3f2a7a5637167cec08f4fa815c1febc4dfc550da1f5d66c45f5ad0f2d4315a0f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w3ykz1du4d9x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-tts/ 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w3ykz1du4d9x_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2504,"output":360,"cacheRead":39200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42064,"cost":{"in